AMANDA Oruh, actor, voice-over artist, and presenter is best known for her role in Kemi Adetiba’s King Of Boys 2 but she has announced her yearning for collaboration with Joke Silva, RMD, and Kemi Adetiba amongst others. The Microbiology graduate, who produced her first feature film entitled ‘Strangers Web’ in 2017 also has a directing credit to her name with the short film ‘Three Faces.’   Tube awards set for 2022 debut in February     Fred Amata says lack of awareness troubling health…     Ubi releases debut single Hapu Ya   “The list of actors’ that I want to collaborate with is so so long, so I would mention a few. Nse Ikpe-Etim, Zainab Balogun, Kelechi Udegbe, Joke Silva, RMD, OC Ukeje, and Blossom Chukwujekwu. In the future when I fully start directing, on my list are Kemi Adetiba, Steve Gukas, James Omokwe, Bolanle Austen-Peters, Kenneth Gyang, Niyi Akinmolayan, Biodun Stephens, Kayode Kasum, AmaPsalmist, Diji Aderogba, Belinda Yanga-Agedah, and Akay Manson, to mention a few.” Read Also: Fred Amata says lack of awareness troubling health insurance in Nollywood Continuing, Oruh says she’s proud of the Nigerian film industry, which is widely referred to as Nollywood. “Firstly, I am proud to be a part of this awesome industry. We are magicians, truly African Magic, and I say this because despite how unfriendly this country is towards a lot of things, little or zero financial support or enabling environment/zero infrastructure to thrive as an industry most of the indie filmmakers go all out to create amazing contents. The progress so far is great to see, I believe strongly in this industry and I know we will get there, that point of excellence, great stories, and delivery.”